13/03/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Support for entrepreneurship and small and medium-sized businesses, promotion of knowledge-based economies and the complete unification of European markets will be Greece's priorities this spring as president of the EU. 
Undersecretary for Press and Mass Media Tilemachos Hitiris provided details during a news conference Wednesday (12 March) about an upcoming European Council meeting in Brussels. 
As for Friday's EU Defence Ministers Council meeting in Athens, Hitiris said it would focus on issues concerning the operational readiness of the Union's rapid reaction forces. 
(MPA - 12/03/03)
